Should it bother me that the Chairman of one of the largest equity funds in the world doesn't know Smith from Ricardo?<p>I guess not.<p>....<p><i>My father wrote in my sixth-grade yearbook quoting Hamlet - Polonius to his son, Laertes: "To thine own self be true."</i><p><pre><code>  No!  I am not Prince Hamlet, nor was meant to be;
  Am an attendant lord [viz, Polonius], one that will do
  To swell a progress, start a scene or two,
  Advise the prince; no doubt, an easy tool,
  Deferential, glad to be of use,
  Politic, cautious, and meticulous;
  Full of high sentence, but a bit obtuse;
  At times, indeed, almost ridiculous--
  Almost, at times, the Fool.</code></pre>
